    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-18T13:27:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-18T13:27:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <head>19. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d19fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 310.387/7–1758. Confidential; Priority. Drafted by <gloss
                            target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>, cleared
                        by <persName corresp="#p_BLE1">Becker</persName> and <gloss target="#t_NE1"
                            >NE</gloss>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_WFO1"
                            >Wilcox</persName> who signed for Dulles. Sent niact to Amman.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-18T14:27:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1958—2:27 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Re Iraqi credentials (<gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_TEL1">tel</gloss> 75 to <gloss target="#t_DEPT1">Dept</gloss>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d19fn2">Telegram 75, July 17, described a conversation with
                            <persName corresp="#p_SCA5">Stavropoulos</persName> regarding the Iraqi
                        rebel government’s designation of Hashim Jawad as Iraq’s Representative at
                        the United Nations. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note>).</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> may inform <persName corresp="#p_SCA5"
                        >Stavropoulos</persName>
                    <gloss target="#t_DEPT1">Dept</gloss> requesting Amembassy Amman suggest to
                        <gloss target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss> that <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>
                    be informed in name King <persName corresp="#p_HIT1">Hussein</persName> that
                    persons purporting to be Iraqi representatives to <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> or <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> body on basis
                    accreditization from Iraqi rebel regime do not in fact represent Iraq. Dept
                    believes such notification could best be justified by referral to July 14
                    announcement <persName corresp="#p_HIT1">Hussein</persName> assuming
                    constitutional authority as President Arab Union, of which Iraq component
                    part.</p>
                <p>Amman is requested take action along above lines.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> For time being <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                        >USG</gloss> would prefer not advise <gloss target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss> on
                    possible assumption now by Arab Union of Iraqi and Jordanian seats in <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>. End <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> may wish inform <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCA5">Stavropoulos</persName> following: <gloss
                        target="#t_DEPT1">Dept</gloss> has instructed all consular posts not issue
                    visa to persons purporting represent Iraqi regime without referral to <gloss
                        target="#t_DEPT1">Dept</gloss>. If Jawad has valid visa it is diffcult to
                    see legal grounds on which he could be denied admission to US if otherwise
                    admissable. If he were to arrive and present credentials to <gloss
                        target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> his seating would then be matter for <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> decision.</p>
                <p>Since above drafted Jawad reported in New York.<note n="3" xml:id="d19fn3">For
                        text of the August 2 U.S. announcement recognizing the Republic of Iraq, see
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 18, 1958, p.
                        273.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
